Menstrual periods is a compulsory rite of passage every natural born female on earth must go through monthly. For some this period can be associated with strong uterine contractions or cramps that can bring about general discomfort to mild or debilitating pain in the lower abdomen, back or groin area. Below are tried and true home remedies that can help alleviate menstrual cramps long term. Heat: Applying heat to your abdomen has been known to help relieve period discomfort. Soak in a warm bath or make use of a hot water bottle to heat your abdomen to relive the cramps. Exercise: Myriad studies have found that physical activities may ease the pain of menstrual cramp, so instead of lying down either engage in light activities, do some chores or hit the gym for some light exercise before during and after your menstrual period. Stress. According to the experts at Mayo Clinic, ”psychological stress may increase your risk of menstrual cramps and their severity”. Vitamins. Eating your vitamins in its raw organic form or through dietary supplements is vital to alleviating menstrual cramps long term. Studies have indicated that vitamin E, omega-3 fatty acids, vitamin B-1 (thiamine), vitamin B-6 and magnesium supplements can effectively reduce menstrual cramps. Herbal tea that contains Fennel and Cinnamon. These herbs are an anti-inflammatory and antispasmodic agent. It can help to ease cramps, fatigue and aches. Add some fresh ginger to the mix and you’ve got a winner.